# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Poker Trainer — environment variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The app is FULLY FUNCTIONAL with ZERO environment variables set.
# Without any keys it runs the built-in Offline Coach (free, instant,
# private). The variables below only enable the optional Cloud Coach.
#
# To use locally: copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in values.
#   cp .env.example .env.local
# `.env.local` is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
# In production, set these in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment
# Variables (NOT in the repo).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Cloud Coach (optional). DeepSeek API key — enables richer phrasing
# and open-ended strategy Q&A. Get one at https://platform.deepseek.com
# This is read ONLY on the server (Next.js Route Handler) and is never
# exposed to the browser. Leave blank/unset to stay fully offline.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=

# Optional: override the DeepSeek base URL or model if needed.
# Defaults are sensible; you usually do not need to set these.
# DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com
# DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-chat
